                <note rend="inline" type="source">717.2114/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-15T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>180. Your 342, September 14, 9 a.m. Has text of treaty been published in Managua?
                    If so the issuance of a statement by the Department would be greatly
                    facilitated. It will be difficult for the Department to make a statement on this
                    subject to the press without giving the general terms of the treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
